# KLIPORA: Architecture lock

## Authoritative source of truth

- **`docs/KLIPORA_SYSTEM_BRAIN.md`** — System architecture, Redis schema, automation flow, agents, key files.
- **`docs/STRATEGIC_BRAIN.md`** — Strategic Brain layer and how it interacts with the system.

These two files are the **authoritative source of truth**. No code or design may contradict them.

## Before modifying any code

1. **Verify alignment** — Confirm the change aligns with the architecture in those docs.
2. **No new systems** — Do not introduce systems, components, or layers outside this architecture.
3. **No local execution scripts** — Do not add or reintroduce scripts that run the pipeline locally (e.g. “run workflow” or “generate video” from CLI). Automation runs only via the defined interfaces (Mission Control API, n8n, Telegram).
4. **Redis is the only memory** — All queues, job store, flags, topic/trend/finance/opportunity state live in Redis (Upstash). Do not add file-based or other memory systems for pipeline state.
5. **n8n is the only automation execution layer** — WF-TREND, WF-GEN, WF-VIDEO, WF-ASSEMBLE (and P2 equivalents) are the automation engine. Do not add alternative workflow runners or execution layers.

## Summary

Read the two docs before architecture or pipeline changes. Redis = memory. n8n = automation. No local execution scripts. No new systems.
